{"TopicId":187338,"ForumId":109,"TopicTitle":"KSP2 Hype Train Thread","CreatedByName":"Whirligig Girl","CreatedById":36077,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-19T20:46:45Z","PageNum":182,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-17T18:45:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224233622\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221676659242\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278303\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerbart\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Kerbart said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m concerned! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust close your eyes and...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWait no, that\u0027s not going to work is it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPretend you\u0027re controlling a very small spacecraft that you want to dock to *insert preferred target here* but your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E controls switches from useles jklwhatever to WASDShiftCtrl.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"shdwlrd","CreatedById":113880,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-17T18:45:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224233617\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221676658581\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022212979\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022gussi111\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, gussi111 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSome people on twitter are claiming that they are seeing fps drops and stuttering in this clip but I can\u0027t really see it? Everything looks good to me.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI didn\u0027t see anything that worried me. It looked to stay at a playable frame rate.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224233619\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221676658792\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150811\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Aziz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, The Aziz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell the framerate isn\u0027t quite stable at times and the camera movements are a bit... laggy-ish, but do we really have to get through all this again?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNope. Had enough of the frame rate discussion. Until you play the game, don\u0027t complain about frame rate. There are too many other reasons for the frame hitches that have nothing to do with the game.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-17T18:46:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224233567\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221676654131\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150811\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Aziz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, The Aziz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo tethers, some people are going to panic.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLike if jetpack was harder than maneuvering a ship with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNewer had tethers in KSP 1 unless you used \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003EKAS\u003C/abbr\u003E winches, and using them almost make it worse.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nBut its challenging for new players and always found the EVA controls a bit award, more in that field of view was not over the head 3rd person as default.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224233621\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221676659119\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022225411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Malathion\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, Malathion said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSuper-HYPED about finally being able to play KSP 2!!!\u00A0 And I\u0027m in the 6:00 am release window, which couldn\u0027t be better IMO.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere is my pre-launch checklist:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Col\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u00A0 Vacation day approved by the boss -\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#e74c3c;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E CHECK\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u00A0 Funds pre-loaded into my Steam account\u00A0 -\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#e74c3c;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E CHECK\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#e74c3c;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u00A0 \u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003EHDMI cable connecting the laptop to the 4k TV -\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#e74c3c;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E CHECK\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u00A0 \u003C/strong\u003EWireless keyboard, headphones, and lap tray staged by the couch\u003Cstrong\u003E \u003C/strong\u003E -\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#e74c3c;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E CHECK\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#e74c3c;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u00A0 \u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003EWife and kids (conveniently) at work and school for the day\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#e74c3c;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E \u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E -\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#e74c3c;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E CHECK\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHelp me out, fellow Kerbalites.\u00A0 What am I missing to make my release-day celebration the best it can be?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd we have an scrub\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:0.0:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_shocked.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:0.0:\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"obney kerman","CreatedById":171373,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-17T18:47:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder what the stock options for customizing your EVA suits will be. Will we get different design templates to pick from? Maybe changing the colors, just the same as with proper ships? If it\u0027s at all possible, I want to give Kerbals different suit stripes for different occupations. Assuming occupations still exist...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-17T18:47:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224233601\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221676656997\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022222736\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mcpattyp\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n40 minutes ago, mcpattyp said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI feel like changing the navball\u2019s location was nothing more than to change something for the sake of changing something. Why move it out of your direct line of sight? It\u2019s \u00A0the most important thing on the screen beside the ship itself. Whatever, it will probably be fixed by a mod in the first week\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s just another one of KSP 1\u0027s mistakes that Intercept has every right to change, another fix to address KSP 1\u0027s horrid UI placement. The middle of the screen is for the rocket. Besides, looking a bit left won\u0027t be difficult, especially now that altitude and speed aren\u0027t scattered on opposite sides of the screen.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224233610\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221676657971\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107350\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SolarAdmiral\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n26 minutes ago, SolarAdmiral said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut I\u0027m also not sure about it, as it is the most important display instrument.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo now it\u0027s the most important display instrument, and it\u0027s been moved a tad to the left. Still just as easy to read as if it were in the middle.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-17T18:48:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224233619\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221676658792\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150811\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Aziz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, The Aziz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell the framerate isn\u0027t quite stable at times and the camera movements are a bit... laggy-ish, but do we really have to get through all this again?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBy Jove (Jool?), yes! Of course I am questioning the framerate of a phone-sized beta screengrab, probably edited two or three times (trimming, resizing) by people who are not professional video editors, uploaded to Tiktok and then converted to Twitter.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn a more serious note: the music is great. I wonder if it\u0027s a looping track or that there\u0027s some procedural generation element in it so that id doesn\u0027t repeat? I play KSP1 without soundtrack because it gets repetitive after a couple of hundred of hours, but at least in the beginning the KSP2 sound will sound fresh.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-17T18:51:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224233601\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221676656997\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022222736\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mcpattyp\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n41 minutes ago, mcpattyp said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI feel like changing the navball\u2019s location was nothing more than to change something for the sake of changing something. Why move it out of your direct line of sight? It\u2019s \u00A0the most important thing on the screen beside the ship itself. Whatever, it will probably be fixed by a mod in the first week\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nThe navball is no longer covering the landing area.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nThe altimeter now is no longer at the opposite side of the navball grouping all the important navigation stuff in the same place.\u00A0\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nThe staging now is consistent with the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E view\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nStaging and craft resources are now at the same side of the screen, grouping together all the important vessel info in the same place.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLike it or not but to me it looks like a lot more thought has gone into this compared to KSP1 layout.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224233610\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221676657971\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107350\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SolarAdmiral\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n29 minutes ago, SolarAdmiral said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think the reason it was moved was due to the thought \u0027most of the rockets you launch are vertical, so if there\u0027s nothing directly above or below, it frees more screen space to see your rocket\u0027.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot only that, monitors are larger than taller, so vertical space is more valuable than horizontal.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SolarAdmiral","CreatedById":107350,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-17T18:51:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224233628\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221676659679\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo now it\u0027s the most important display instrument, and it\u0027s been moved a tad to the left. Still just as easy to read as if it were in the middle.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeh I\u0027m not mad about it or even sure it will be a bad change. Even if we can move them, I\u0027m going to give it a good try as is first to see how it works in the new layout.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-17T18:55:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224233631\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221676659886\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107350\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SolarAdmiral\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, SolarAdmiral said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeh I\u0027m not mad about it or even sure it will be a bad change. Even if we can move them, I\u0027m going to give it a good try as is first to see how it works in the new layout.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve been playing with the navball shoved all the way left as far as possible for years. It made sense to me to keep the center clear. Glad it\u0027s the default in KSP2.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-02-17T18:59:14Z\u0022 title=\u002202/17/2023 06:59  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 17, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Kerbart\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snark","CreatedById":125662,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-17T18:57:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224233566\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221676654023\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022105624\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Pthigrivi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Pthigrivi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll these little animations are SO good now. Absolute love. And the little ladder sound effects!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFingers on the suit gloves!\u00A0 No more mittens!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"whatsEJstandfor","CreatedById":220814,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-17T19:28:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224233619\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221676658792\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150811\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Aziz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n53 minutes ago, The Aziz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell the framerate isn\u0027t quite stable at times and the camera movements are a bit... laggy-ish, but do we really have to get through all this again?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, seriously. Everyone will get to find out for themselves in less than a week. If I see another g*sh d*ng thread pop up speculating about performance I\u0027m going to fl*p\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stephensan","CreatedById":222320,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-17T19:31:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHoly MF christ the specs are tough swallow...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni don\u0027t even got the recommended PC for GPU.. like\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022KSP2-SPECS-v7-FINAL-Poppe_Version-3-plsl\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022164.00\u0022 height=\u0022674\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/1039965330774175784/1076223449971818556/KSP2-SPECS-v7-FINAL-Poppe_Version-3-plsletthisbefinal-2.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-02-17T19:32:03Z\u0022 title=\u002202/17/2023 07:32  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 17, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Stephensan\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LHACK4142","CreatedById":208897,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-17T19:31:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=31GRu9OYuVM\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=31GRu9OYuVM\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stephensan","CreatedById":222320,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-17T19:32:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224233657\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221676662299\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022208897\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022LHACK4142\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, LHACK4142 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=31GRu9OYuVM\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=31GRu9OYuVM\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYES, excatly\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snark","CreatedById":125662,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-17T19:33:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224233163\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221676584210\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022192535\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MARL_Mk1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 hours ago, MARL_Mk1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust... hear me out. I\u0027m not the best at Gimp, the Photoshop of the poor, but I tried my best:\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nIncreased size of Ball, glued the indicators to the diagonals instead of having them hang on the sides. Looks way tidier and cleaner.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/6jxpJvV.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00226jxpJvV.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002260.00\u0022 height=\u0022487\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/6jxpJvV.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nY\u0027know, I was thinking about all the really excellent discussions people have been having about the new navball (really excellent photoshopping here, by the way!), and realizing that different people like different things, and then was thinking about this comment I made yesterday,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224233085\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221676577262\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022125662\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Snark\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n23 hours ago, Snark said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(I look forward to seeing what modders do to offer alternate navball styling.\u00A0 Betcha that\u0027s gonna be a hot topic.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...and was just now reminded about a comment from Nate Simpson way back in 2019, when I had a chance to interview him:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223663904\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187832\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221567222710\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022125662\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Snark\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 8/30/2019 at 11:38 PM, Snark said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EQ:\u00A0 How customizable will the UI be?\u00A0 (navball position, etc.)\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EA:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0 They want to make it very flexible.\u00A0 They\u0027re trying to make the UI more easily moddable than before.\u00A0 As for player-customizability, details are still TBD.\u00A0 They\u0027re aware that players can be very particular about how UI elements are arranged, and want to make people happy.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s been a \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Elot\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E of water under the bridge since then, and who knows what they\u0027ve actually had the time and budget to do, so I\u0027m not exactly going to take that to the bank.\u00A0 But at least it shows that they were \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Ethinking\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E about it, even then, and that their hearts are in the right place, which I find encouraging.\u00A0 Guess we\u0027ll find out soon.\u00A0 \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mcpattyp","CreatedById":222736,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-17T19:34:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDamn my 2070 is just barely above the minimum\u2026 wait\u2026 3080 \u00A0RECOMMENDED???!!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sunforge","CreatedById":225145,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-17T19:34:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224233656\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221676662285\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022222320\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Stephensan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Stephensan said:\n\u003C/div\u0